    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The layout of `position:fixed` descendants is not a bug.  It's in the standard (http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-transforms/#transform-property).  It does break some assumptions, though, that fixed position elements are positioned relative to the viewport.\n\n(well, I guess it could be both a \"bug\" and in the standards, but we'll leave that discussion for another day)\n"
  },
