    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Seems to violate the definition of fixed positioning, and the spec itself seems to have some arguing about why on earth it would have that effect, when it doesn't make any sense, but yes, it does appear to be in the spec, apparently as an unintended, but resigned-to side effect of implementation challenges, rather than by design. The behavior is listed as a bug on Chrome, at least.\n"
